        "1.The formula for the PERT expectation is:$E[X] = \\frac{a + 4c + b}{6}$\n",
        "\n",
        "We are given the condition that the expected time must equal the most likely time.\n",
        "therefore we set E[x] = c.\n",
        "\n",
        "$c = \\frac{a + 4c + b}{6}$\n",
        "therefore b = 17.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "2.$Var(X) = \\frac{(E[X]-a)(b-E[X])}{7}$)\n",
        "\n",
        "$Var(X) = \\frac{(11 - 5)(17 - 11)}{7}$\n",
        "$Var(X) = \\frac{6 \\times 6}{7}  \\approx \\mathbf{5.14}$"
